### TL;DR

v0.1.47 published. v0.1.48 must ship BEFORE the 3-machine mesh test fires. Two P0 scopes block the test:

1. **SKU Model Promotion (P0):** v0.1.47 diagnostic shows `sku.tier = full` but Ollama is serving `qwen2.5:0.5b` (floor model). `gemma4:12b` manifest exists on disk. Full-tier must run `gemma4:12b` — without this fix, mesh test results are not comparable to Google's published 77.2% / 78.8% benchmarks on gemma4:12b.

2. **Mesh Glance Page (P0):** Founder's wife needs to watch mesh test progress from her phone on the couch while the test runs on the home network. LAN-visible HTML page, auto-refresh every 30s, per-node progress bars, ETA countdown. No JS framework. Heartbeat canon compliance.

Both P0s gate the mesh test. If P1+P2 would delay ship of P0s, Knight may stage v0.1.48-alpha with just P0s and bundle P1+P2 into v0.1.48 proper — flag the decision in the Yoke-return.

